All ASP.NET Core apps reference `DedgeAuth.Client` for authentication. All run as IIS virtual applications under `Default Web Site` on port 80.

## Publish: Single App

Each app has its own `Build-And-Publish.ps1` at its repo root. This publishes to the **staging share** on `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\DedgeCommon\Software\DedgeWinApps\<AppName>`.

```powershell
# DedgeAuth (also deploys DedgePsh server scripts)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\Build-And-Publish.ps1"

# DocView
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DocView\Build-And-Publish.ps1"

# GenericLogHandler (publishes WebApi + ImportService + AlertAgent)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\GenericLogHandler\Build-And-Publish.ps1"

# ServerMonitorDashboard (publishes Dashboard + Agent + TrayIcon + Dashboard.Tray)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\ServerMonitor\Build-And-Publish.ps1"

# AutoDocJson
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\AutoDocJson\Build-And-Publish.ps1"
```

All use the `WebApp-FileSystem.pubxml` publish profile. Version bumps are Patch by default.

## Publish: All Apps at Once

```powershell
# Build DedgeAuth first, then all consumer apps referencing DedgeAuth.Client
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1"

# Dry run (show what would build without building)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1" -DryRun

# Skip DedgeAuth, only rebuild consumer apps
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1" -SkipDedgeAuth
```

