## PowerShell Module: IIS-Handler

All IIS operations are powered by the **IIS-Handler** PowerShell module:

| Item | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Module** | `IIS-Handler` |
| **Source** | `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\_Modules\IIS-Handler\IIS-Handler.psm1` |
| **On PSModulePath** | Yes -- loaded via `Import-Module IIS-Handler -Force` |
| **Key functions** | `Deploy-IISSite`, `Uninstall-IISSite`, `Test-IISSite`, `Install-OurWinApp` |

`Deploy-IISSite` implements the 10-step deploy process: Teardown → Install files → Create app pool → Create virtual app → Generate web.config → Set permissions → Firewall rules → Start → Verify → Health check.

## IIS-DeployApp Scripts

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `IIS-DeployApp.ps1` | Deploy/update one app from template |
| `IIS-UninstallApp.ps1` | Remove one virtual app + app pool + firewall |
| `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` | Teardown all + iisreset + redeploy all from templates |
| `Test-IISSite.ps1` | Diagnostics and health checks |
| `_deploy.ps1` | Sync scripts and templates to servers |

All located in: `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\`

## Full Deploy Sequence

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\GrabScreenShot\Invoke-GrabScreenShot.ps1"
```

## Impact Rules

- **Changing DedgeAuth.Client** → rebuild ALL consumer apps (`Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1`) then `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1`
- **Changing DedgeAuth wwwroot (CSS/JS/HTML)** → rebuild DedgeAuth only; consumer apps fetch assets via proxy
- **Changing a single consumer app** → rebuild that app only, then `IIS-DeployApp.ps1 -SiteName <name>`
- **Changing deploy templates** → run `IIS-DeployApp\_deploy.ps1` to sync to servers, then `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1`
- **Changing IIS-Handler.psm1** → commit to DedgePsh, run `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` to pick up changes
